From: Eric Dumazet <edumazet@google.com>
Date: Fri, 31 Jan 2020 10:22:47 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] tcp: clear tp->delivered in tcp_disconnect()
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.5.3
Git-commit: 2fbdd56251b5c62f96589f39eded277260de7267

[ Upstream commit 2fbdd56251b5c62f96589f39eded277260de7267 ]

tp->delivered needs to be cleared in tcp_disconnect().

tcp_disconnect() is rarely used, but it is worth fixing it.

Fixes: ddf1af6fa00e ("tcp: new delivery accounting")
Signed-off-by: Eric Dumazet <edumazet@google.com>
Cc: Yuchung Cheng <ycheng@google.com>
Cc: Neal Cardwell <ncardwell@google.com>
Acked-by: Yuchung Cheng <ycheng@google.com>
Acked-by: Neal Cardwell <ncardwell@google.com>
Acked-by: Soheil Hassas Yeganeh <soheil@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 net/ipv4/tcp.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/net/ipv4/tcp.c b/net/ipv4/tcp.c
index 4f1f7ec46ffc..3cca00d78b3e 100644
--- a/net/ipv4/tcp.c
+++ b/net/ipv4/tcp.c
@@ -2621,6 +2621,7 @@ int tcp_disconnect(struct sock *sk, int flags)
 	tp->snd_cwnd = TCP_INIT_CWND;
 	tp->snd_cwnd_cnt = 0;
 	tp->window_clamp = 0;
+	tp->delivered = 0;
 	tp->delivered_ce = 0;
 	tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_Open);
 	tp->is_sack_reneg = 0;
